The paper deals with deep learning architectures for semantic segmentation, which is a computer vision task. Therefore, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also discusses network compression and pyramid representation, which are related to machine learning and artificial intelligence, making cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) likely sub-categories as well. The paper also mentions factorized convolution, which is a technique used in neural networks, making cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) a possible sub-category. Finally, the paper discusses the Cityscapes dataset, which is related to natural language processing and computer vision, making cs.CL (Computation and Language) a less likely but still possible sub-category.
